Program: Omnibus
Title: Going Back to the Roots
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p0376mc0
Last Broadcast Date: 06 February 2002
'It's the way we used to farm'. A look at organic farming in Africa and a project in Luangwa National Park in Zambia to designate an area rich in oil seeds and honey as organic. Contributors include Susy Burgess,Valentine Chitalu and Adrian Carr.